  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel your<strong> red onion[s]</strong> and slice some rings off (2 per person!) as finely as you can, then dice the <strong>remaining red onion</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> onion rings</strong> and your<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>to a shallow bowl and set aside to pickle until serving – these are your <strong>quick-pickled onion rings</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624887920425-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624887920425-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624887920425-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624887920425-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1624887920425-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion </strong>and <strong>diced pepper</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624887924557-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624887924557-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624887924557-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624887924557-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1624887924557-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>coriander</strong> as finely as you can, including the stalks</p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo </strong>with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and the <strong>chopped coriander </strong>in a small bowl<strong> </strong>– this is your <strong>herby mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624887930915-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624887930915-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624887930915-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624887930915-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1624887930915-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p><p>Once the onion has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and<strong> drained black beans</strong> to the pan</p><p>Add your<strong> ground smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>soy sauce</strong>, then cook for a further 5-6 min or until the black beans are starting to crisp – these are your <strong>smoky black beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1624887937017-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1624887937017-x400.jpg",
